Hi, I received a conversion (qualified lead) on my survey/ landing page, but the conversion is not showing in Ads Manager. I already tested the pixel and it signaled that it was tracking properly. Does it usually just take some time for the conversion to show in platform?

Hey there! It sounds like you've done a great job testing your pixel. Typically, conversions should appear in Ads Manager relatively quickly, but there can be a slight delay depending on the reporting method used. If you're using the 'Ad Management' tab, it should be real-time. However, if you're checking through custom reports under the 'Reports' tab or via API, there might be a 2-3 hour delay. If the conversion still doesn't show up after this time frame, you might want to double-check your setup or reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance.
The conversion happened last night around midnight, so it's been 10 hours.

Since it's been 10 hours, the conversion should have appeared in Ads Manager by now. If it's still not showing, there might be an issue with the setup or tracking. I recommend checking your event management settings to ensure everything is configured correctly. If everything seems fine and the issue persists, please reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for more detailed assistance.
